The paper discusses a model-based test case generation algorithm for information and Internet of Things systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories. The algorithm involves prioritizing certain parts of software system workflows based on business priority, which could also fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also compares the proposed algorithm with five alternatives using various metrics, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
